  <div class="comment-content">

    <div class="edit-comment-hide">
      <div class="comment-body markdown-body markdown-format js-comment-body">
          <p>One of our users reported a strange bug: when rotating the device several times in a very short times, mapsforge crashes with a null pointer exception. (for reference <a href="https://code.google.com/p/openbmap/issues/detail?id=72">https://code.google.com/p/openbmap/issues/detail?id=72</a>)</p>

<p>Version is mapsforge-0.5.0.<br>
I can reproduce the NPE on my Nexus 4 device (although I need to shake for several seconds and it doesn't happen in every case)</p>

<p>Relevant log cat from my Nexus 4:<br>
02-28 20:43:26.710 E/AndroidRuntime(15442): Caused by: java.lang.NullPointerException<br>
02-28 20:43:26.710 E/AndroidRuntime(15442):     at org.mapsforge.map.layer.cache.FileSystemTileCache.deleteDirectory(FileSystemTileCache.java:99)<br>
