  <div class="comment-content">

    <div class="edit-comment-hide">
      <div class="comment-body markdown-body markdown-format js-comment-body">
          <p>That code doesn't create a threaded cache.<br>
But you're using fixed values for memory and file cache sizes (probably from AWT sample).</p>

<p>I recommend to use one of <code>AndroidUtil.createTileCache</code> methods which perform the needed calculations for cache size based on device characteristics.</p>

<p>You can check <a href="https://github.com/mapsforge/mapsforge/blob/master/docs/Getting-Started-Android-App.md">Getting-Started-Android-App</a> wiki for a complete implementation.</p>

<p>About activity restart you can read also <a href="https://groups.google.com/d/msg/mapsforge-dev/7Mem4S1Aotw/ryJJqB2Li4MJ">here</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
